  <header>
    <h1>The Page Turners Society</h1>
    <p>Gatton Academy's Book Club — Discover, Discuss, and Delight in Great Reads</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Monthly Meeting Schedule</h2>
    <p>We meet <strong>once a week</strong>. The exact day and time will be decided and voted upon by members.</p>
    <p>Below are our <strong>current monthly themes</strong> for engaging and diverse reading experiences:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>September</strong><br />
        Coming of Age & Self-Discovery — Stories about growth, identity, and finding your place.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>October</strong><br />
        Spooky, Supernatural & Mystery — Get ready for thrilling and eerie reads perfect for fall.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>November</strong><br />
        Social Justice & Activism — Powerful stories about standing up and making a difference.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>December/January</strong><br />
        Winter Break: Cozy Reads & Reflection — Heartwarming books and time to reflect on the year.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>February</strong><br />
        Love & Friendship — Celebrate all kinds of connections and relationships.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>March</strong><br />
        Fantasy & Adventure — Dive into magical worlds and epic quests.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>April</strong><br />
        Mental Health & Wellness — Books focusing on emotional well-being and resilience.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>May</strong><br />
        Diverse Voices & Cultures — Explore stories from a variety of backgrounds and experiences.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Weekly Meeting Format</h2>
    <p>Each month’s theme will include four weekly meetings with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Week 1: Introductions & theme overview</li>
      <li>Week 2: Deep discussion on characters and plot</li>
      <li>Week 3: Creative activity related to the book (writing, art, games)</li>
      <li>Week 4: Wrap-up, sharing favorites, and voting on next month’s book</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

